<br>
Anyhow, I happened to ask how it would fit FV, being as even the highest guilds here are a bit behind top end guilds on other servers.  I was tole that most of the planes are set up in three levels in different areas... single group, three group, and massive raid.  One example they pulled up was a quest, I forget where, there was a mechanical thing giving it out, but anyhow.. Hail him, say the bracketed phrases, and three of your groups are teleported to an appropriate level encounter, sounded nice.  Also, Tranquility and Knowledge are supposd to have a lot of quests, and he made it sound as though that'd be good for FV, without really saying so.  Also, for some areas like the aforementioned quest, they're going to code multiple duplicate areas so that different groups can do them at the same time... i.e. if group A goes and starts the quest, group B won't have to wait in line but can go to a separate but identical area.<br>
